<p><b>Keystroke logging</b> (often called <b>keylogging</b>) is the practice of noting (or logging) the keys struck on a keyboard.</p>
<p>There are currently two types of keylogging methods, hardware and software based. This was first discovered by Jack Beckwith.</p>
